<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1891-10-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1891-10-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="194" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d194">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Sir <persName type="from">Julian
                                    Pauncefote</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Wharton</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">British
                                        Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-10-12"><hi rend="italic">October 12,
                                1891</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your note of the 10th instant inclosing copy of a memorial
                            from the Lake Carriers’ Association of Buffalo complaining of
                            discrimination by the Canadian Government against citizens of the United
                            States in the use of the Welland Canal in contravention of article 27 of
                            the treaty of 1871, and to inform you at the same time that I will bring
                            this matter to the attention of my Government.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Julian
                            Pauncefote.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>